      <tr>
        <td>
          <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2"><b><a name="General Raid rules and Guidelines">General
          Raid rules and Guidelines</a></b></font></p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2"><b>Time of Raid:<br>
              &nbsp;</b></font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#FFFF99">All
                  participants and alternates MUST be at the raid entry point AT
                  LEAST 30 Minutes before the scheduled raid time.&nbsp;<br>
                  &nbsp;</font></font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#FFFF99">Transport
                  to the raid site after the raid has begun will be the
                  responsibility of the player.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font></font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#FFFF99">TP'ers
                  will not be asked to leave a raid in progress to<br>
                  pick up someone who is late.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font></font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font color="#FFFF99" face="Arial" size="2">If
                  you are late, please check with the Raid Coordinator prior to
                  coming.&nbsp; Depending on the location and progress of the
                  raid, you may or may not be able to get there.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><b><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF00">Stand
                      By:<br>
                      &nbsp;</font></b>
                      <ul>
                        <li>
                          <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">Anyone
                          who is not at the raid entry point by 15 minutes
                          before the scheduled raid time may be replaced by any
                          alternate at the sole discretion of the Raid Leader.</font><font color="#FFFF99" face="Arial" size="2"><br>
                          &nbsp;</font></li>
                      </ul>
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF00"><b>Bind
              Points:</b></font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">All
                  participants must be bound either at the point specified in
                  the details of the raid listing or at the nearest city for
                  non-binding classes.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b>Minimum
              Time Commintment:</b></font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">Do
                  not attend if you cannot commit to be present for the entire
                  raid, or for at least five (5) hours on weekends (Fri-Sun) or
                  three (3) hours on weekdays (Mon-Thur).&nbsp; Time will be
                  longer for Planes Raids.&nbsp;&nbsp; This does not apply to
                  &quot;impromptu&quot; raids and/or mini raids.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><b><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF00">Preparation:</font></b>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" color="#FFFF99" face="Arial">Print
                  and read the appropriate guides and maps for the raid you plan
                  to attend, and make sure your questions are answered before
                  the raid. There isn’t time to ask them during the raid!<br>
                  &nbsp;</font></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b><a name="Raid Leader">Raid
          Leader</a></b></font></p>
          <p align="left"><font size="2" color="#FFFF99" face="Arial">The raid
          leader is the person who will choose what strategy or tactics to use.
          On a raid, the Raid Leader's word is absolute. If he/she says charge,
          we charge. If he/she says camp, we camp. If he/she tells you to die,
          you die! Do not question his/her decisions, and do not try to make
          decisions for him/her. You can argue with him/her all you want after
          the raid, but during the raid, follow him/her no matter what.<br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">There
              is only ONE raid leader for each raid. He/she is the one
              responsible for gathering ALL information, so various members will
              get a /tell from him/her throughout the raid, asking for
              specifics.<br>
              &nbsp;</font></li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">If
              he/she doesn't ask, assume that he/she knows.&nbsp;<br>
              &nbsp;</font></li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">The
              raid leader's /tell lines are to be kept clear by everyone
              attending the raid. Trust me, he/she is way to busy to answer
              questions and carry on a conversation. Sometimes it's hard to tell
              people you are busy without being rude, so keep this from
              happening by not bothering him/her.<br>
              &nbsp;</font></li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">No one
              should send /tells to the raid leader unless he/she /tells you
              first.<br>
              &nbsp;</font></li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">The
              Raid Leader gives ALL the orders, and should be the only person to
              use /shout while *speaking* to the raid. No one else except the
              raid leader should be giving any sort of commands to the raid.
              (with one exception, see below)<br>
              &nbsp;</font></li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">The
              Raid Leader is responsible for dismissing a raider from the raid
              because of conduct unbecoming of a Dragon’s Revolt
              member/recruit.<br>
              &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">First
                  offense of a specific type, warning</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">2nd
                  offense of the same type, 2nd warning</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">-3rd
                  offense of the same type, dismissal<br>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Offenses:<br>
                      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font>
                      <ul>
                        <li>
                          <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Being
                          rude to fellow raid members</font></li>
                        <li>
                          <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Not
                          paying attention to orders</font></li>
                        <li>
                          <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Not
                          following any of the guidelines listed here</font></li>
                        <li>
                          <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">-Making
                          a scene because of something he doesn't like<br>
                          &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></li>
                      </ul>
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">It
                  is up to the Raid Leader's discretion when determining the
                  seriousness of the offense. Minor mistakes are fine, but major
                  ones such as disrespecting a fellow raider can result in
                  immediate dismissal.<br>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">After
                  the raid the Raid Leader will submit his side of the situation
                  on the message-board under the Officer forum to be discussed
                  among the Officers and Guild Leaders.<br>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">The
              Raid Leader is also responsible for keeping the raid force updated
              on what is happening, such as telling the raid force we have to be
              patient because the puller died and we are doing corpse run. If he
              is silent for a while and everything seem to be at a standstill,
              it's up to the Raid Coordinator (below) to /tell him and ask
              what's going on.<br>
              &nbsp;</font></li>
          </ul>
          <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b><a name="Raid Coordinator">Raid
          Coordinator</a></b></font></p>
          <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">This
          person has been appointed by the Guild Leader to schedule raids and to
          handle the normal problems that happen on raids. He/she is in charge
          of keeping track of how many people are at the raid, who's logging,
          and who's incoming. When people ask to speak to the Raid Leader about
          attendance, send them to the Raid Coordinator.<br>
          &nbsp;</font></p>
          <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b><a name="Communications">Communications</a></b></font></p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b>Tells<br>
              &nbsp;</b></font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Tells
                  and requests should not be sent to the following individuals
                  by raid participants.&nbsp; They are very busy performing
                  their assigned tasks and ensuring that the raid proceeds as
                  planned.&nbsp; If you have an issue that needs immediate
                  resolution/attention, please funnel it though your group
                  leader.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Raid
                      Leader</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Raid
                      Coordinator</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Main
                      Assist</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Puller<br>
                      &nbsp;</font></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b>Channels<br>
              &nbsp;</b></font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">All
                  raids will be conducted on the &quot;DRraid&quot;
                  channel.&nbsp; The channel password is the same as the
                  password used to access the member forums.<br>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">A
                  second channel, &quot;DRgrp&quot; is in place for use by the
                  raid leader, coordinator, group leader, MA, SA and
                  puller.&nbsp; This channel should be reserved for
                  communications among those people.&nbsp; The raid leader will
                  provide the password at the time of the raid.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">It
                  is suggested that you turn off /guild and /auction during a
                  raid so that you will not be distracted.&nbsp; /ooc and /shout
                  can be left on as there may be non-raiders in the raid zone
                  providing information and warnings.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Those
                  on the raid should only be using the general raid and raid
                  leader channels.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Nobody
                  should be carrying on conversation with /say, /ooc, or /shout
                  and Emotes should be avoided.&nbsp; All of these create
                  distractions and vital raid infomation and instructions can be
                  missed.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b><a name="Raid Specifics">Raid
          Specifics</a></b></font></p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b>/ASSIST<br>
              &nbsp;</b></font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">All
                  raid participants should create a </font><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b>/ASSIST</b></font><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">
                  hotkey.&nbsp; The raid leader will instruct on the name of the
                  person that will be the MA at the beginning of the raid.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Set
                      up </font><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b>/ASSIST</b></font><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">
                      as follows:<br>
                      /assist off<br>
                      /assist {Insert name of MA here]<br>
                      &nbsp;</font></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b>Incoming
              and Assist Messages<br>
              &nbsp;&nbsp;</b></font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">The
                  puller will have one message that states:<br>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;</font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Incoming
                      %T.&nbsp; Get ready.<br>
                      &nbsp;&nbsp;</font></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">The
                  MA should have the following keys set up.&nbsp; Remember, the
                  puller and MA can and often will be the same person on lower
                  level raids.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Attack
                      %T NOW!</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Switching
                      attack to %T.<br>
                      &nbsp;</font></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00">DO
                  NOT</font><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99"> attack
                  as soon as you see the incoming message.<br>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;</font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Melee
                      should wait for the &quot;Attack %T NOW!&quot; message
                      before activating attack.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Casters
                      should wait until approx 75% health on the mob before
                      engaging.<br>
                      &nbsp;</font></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b><a name="Puller">Puller</a><br>
              &nbsp;</b></font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">The
                  puller for our raids will preferably be a monk or shadowknight
                  because of their ability to Feign Death and avoid trains/split
                  mobs.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">The
                  puller will be announced by the raid leader at the beginning
                  of the raid.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">If
                  the puller gets too many mobs for the group to handle, they
                  should die as close to camp as possible without training the
                  raid group and causing a wipeout.<br>
                  </font></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b><a name="Main Assist">Main
              Assist</a><br>
              &nbsp;</b></font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">The
                  Main Assist for our raids will preferably be a warrior.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">The
                  Main Assist if not the same as the puller should /assist the
                  puller to target the mob being pulled.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">If
                  the puller is splitting mobs the MA should try tagging the
                  targeted mob with a range weapon or spell if available.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Your
                  job is </font><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b>NOT
                  </b></font><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">to try
                  and out-taunt the MA and get agro.&nbsp; Your job is to wait
                  for the MA to gain sufficient agro and call for attack.<br>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b><a name="SA - Secondary /ASSIST">SA
              - Secondary /ASSIST</a></b></font><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99"><br>
              </font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">In
                  some zones there are mobs that are uncharmable and
                  unmezzable.&nbsp; If we are raiding a zone like this, a SA
                  will be assigned at the beginning of the raid and some groups
                  will be told to /assist MA and others will be assigned to
                  /assist the SA.&nbsp; Everyone should be using /ASSIST unless
                  the puller advises additional mobs and offtanking is
                  needed.&nbsp; In that Situation, you should /assist the MA or
                  SA as was assigned to you at the beginning of the raid.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><a name="Taunter">Taunter</a><br>
              </font></b>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">This
                  person will be assigned at the beginning of the raid by the
                  raid leader.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">The
                  taunter will serve as a normal melee unless there is an add
                  that cannot be rooted/mezzed or somehow gotten under lockdown
                  by the casters.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">In
                      this situation the taunter will disengage from the main
                      melee fight to taunt the mob off of the casters until they
                      are able to gain control of the situation.&nbsp; At that
                      time they should return to the main fight and assist the
                      main.<br>
                      &nbsp;</font></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><a name="Melee classes">Melee
              classes</a><br>
              &nbsp;</font></b>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Wait
                  until Attack is called by the MA.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">At
                  that time, attack the mob.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Remember,
                  you are not here to gain the agro of the mob away from the MA.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b><a name="Priest classes">Priest
              classes</a><br>
              &nbsp;</b></font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00">Clerics<br>
                  &nbsp;</font></b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Main
                      function will be to heal the melee</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Heal
                      casters if needed.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Provide
                      HP/AC buffs as needed</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Rezz
                      as needed</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Stun
                      mobs that complete heal</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Root
                      adds as needed.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">If
                      there are multiple clerics present, you should communicate
                      with each other and decide on what the main duties of each
                      of you will be.<br>
                      &nbsp;</font></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b>Shaman</b></font><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99"><br>
                  &nbsp;</font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">1
                      shaman will be assigned to slow the mob.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">If
                      there is a cleric in your group, your primary healing
                      should be done on the casters.&nbsp; You can back up heal
                      for the cleric on the melees as needed.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Provide
                      buffs as needed.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Root
                      adds as needed.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">If
                      there are multiple shaman present, you should communicate
                      with each other and decide on what the main duties of each
                      of you will be.<br>
                      &nbsp;</font></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b>Druids<br>
                  &nbsp;</b></font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Primary
                      duty is caster healing.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Heal
                      melee if there is no cleric present or cleric in your
                      group needs assistance.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Debuff,
                      such as snare, mob as needed</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Buff
                      raid participants as needed</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Druids
                      will also be needed to provide transportation to and from
                      raids.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">If
                      there are multiple druids present, you should communicate
                      with each other and decide on what the main duties of each
                      of you will be.<br>
                      &nbsp;</font></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Under
                  no circumstances should any priest classes be practicing their
                  melee skills.&nbsp; A raid is not the appropriate time nor
                  place for this.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b><a name="Int Casters">Int
              Casters</a><br>
              &nbsp;</b></font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b>Enchanters<br>
                  &nbsp;</b></font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Provide
                      clarity to all mana users</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Provide
                      a form of haste for melee types</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font color="#FFFF99" face="Arial" size="2">Tash
                      on mob</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font color="#FFFF99" face="Arial" size="2">Slow
                      mob if no shaman is available</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Mezz
                      adds as needed</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Charm
                      unmezzable adds as needed</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Memblur
                      on mobs that have agroed on other casters.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">If
                      and only if you are at 70m or more, it is acceptable to
                      throw an occasional nuke on the mob.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">If
                      there are multiple enchanters present, you should
                      communicate with each other and decide on what the main
                      duties of each of you will be.<br>
                      &nbsp;</font></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b>Wizzards<br>
                  &nbsp;</b></font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Nuke</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Transportation
                      to and from the raid location as needed.<br>
                      &nbsp;</font></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b>Mages<br>
                  &nbsp;</b></font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Nuke</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Summon
                      items as needed by raid members</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">CoH
                      if needed and available</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Pets
                      - DO NOT cast pets unless we are at a fixed camp site.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">If
                      we do move to another site, get rid of it and re-cast it
                      when we arrive, or guard it in a safe location and summon
                      it to you upon arrival.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Remember,
                      only 4 pets can attack any given mob.&nbsp; If there are
                      more than 4 mages present, work it out amongst yourselves
                      which of you will be casting pets.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">If
                      you loose pet control for any reason, either use the /pet
                      get lost command or invis yourself.<br>
                      &nbsp;</font></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b>Necros</b></font><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99"><br>
                  &nbsp;</font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Mana
                      dump on Clerics and other casters as needed.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Pets
                      - DO NOT cast pets unless we are at a fixed camp site.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">If
                      we do move to another site, get rid of it and re-cast it
                      when we arrive, or guard it in a safe location and summon
                      it to you upon arrival.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Remember,
                      only 4 pets can attack any given mob.&nbsp; If there are
                      more than 4 mages present, work it out amongst yourselves
                      which of you will be casting pets.</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">If
                      you loose pet control for any reason, either use the /pet
                      get lost command or invis yourself.<br>
                      &nbsp;</font></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b><a name="Loot">Loot</a></b></font></p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b>ONLY</b></font><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">
              the group leader of the kill group should be looting, in some cases
              when the group leader is full or has additional responsibilities,
              they may assign this task to another group member.<br>
              &nbsp;</font></li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">The
              looter should call out on the main raid channel what is dropped by
              each mob.<br>
              &nbsp;</font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Call
                  out as follows<br>
                  &nbsp;</font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">coin</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">sellable
                      (This would be the common and junk items below.&nbsp; To
                      save time, jsut call out &quot;sellable&quot;</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">research</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">If
                      an item drops that will be rolled on, DO NOT call it out
                      on general raid chat.&nbsp; Call out item name, stats, and
                      classes that can use it on the raid leader channel.</font><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99"><br>
                      &nbsp;&nbsp;</font></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b>Coin
              and Common/Junk Items<br>
              &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</b></font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Looters
                  should turn all coin and sellable over to the Raid Leader
                  after the raid has ended.<br>
                  </font></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b>Research
              Items</b></font><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99"><br>
              &nbsp;</font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Call
                  out Research on the main raid channel</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Turn
                  these items over to the RL at the end of the raid.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Research
                  items will either be distributed at the end of the raid, or
                  placed on the guild research mule for distribution at a swap
                  meet.<br>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;</font></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00"><b>Class
              specific armor and weapons<br>
              &nbsp;&nbsp;</b></font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">These
                  items will be announced in the general raid channel by the
                  raid leader.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">DO
                  NOT roll until you are instructed to do so.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Be
                  prepared to roll when the roll is called for.&nbsp; Early or
                  late rolls will not be accepted.&nbsp; It is your
                  responsibility to pay attention and roll at the appropriate
                  time.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">You
                  may win 1 and only 1 piece of class specific armor per raid.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Once
                  everyone in your class has won an item, you will be eligible
                  to roll on a 2nd, 3rd, etc... item.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">If
                  you ALREADY have the item in question, you should pass on it
                  and allow your other raid members an opportunity to also
                  posses that item.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">if
                  you have BETTER than the item being rolled on, you should
                  consider those on the raid for which the item would actually
                  be an upgrade.<br>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">Some
                  item that drop are </font><b><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF00">NOT
                  </font></b><font size="2" face="Arial" color="#FFFF99">class
                  specific but will be considered as class specific based on
                  their stats.<br>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;</font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">For
                      example, a Cloak of Flames is ALL/ALL regarding race and
                      class, yet obviously this item should be rolled on amongst
                      the melee for it's Haste effect.<br>
                      &nbsp;&nbsp;</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">Other
                      items that are ALL/ALL and have certain stats may also go
                      to a specific class.&nbsp; Items with high CHA will be
                      rolled on by chanters and bards.<br>
                      &nbsp;</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">Wisdom
                      Items among the priest classes.<br>
                      &nbsp;</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">Intel
                      items among Intel casters, etc...<br>
                      &nbsp;</font></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">If
                  you would win the above Cloak of Flames in the example, this
                  would count as your Melee specific win and you would not roll
                  again until all other melees have won a melee item.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">You
                  may win multiple items if you are the only class of your type
                  on the raid and multiple specific items drop for your class.<br>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;</font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">For
                      example, if you are the </font><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF00">ONLY</font><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">
                      Mage on the raid and multiple MAGE only items drop, they
                      will be awarded to you by default.<br>
                      &nbsp;</font></li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">In
                      this case should an item come up for roll by all int
                      casters, you would not roll on it untill all int casters
                      have won an item.<br>
                      &nbsp;</font></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">You
                  may pass on item if you prefer to wait and have a chance at
                  something that may drop later.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">If
                      a class specific item drops, and all others in your class
                      have won, you will get the item by default.&nbsp; Passing
                      on it will NOT make you win the next class specific item
                      by default.&nbsp; If you still choose to pass on this
                      item, all others in your class WILL be able to roll on the
                      next available item.&nbsp; Please keep this in mind when
                      deciding to pass on items.&nbsp; You may not work this to
                      your advantage to get a specific item by default.</font></li>
                  </ul>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF00"><b>Open
              rolls<br>
              </b></font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">Some
                  items that drop will not be considered for a specific class,
                  such as an ALL/ALL item that has resists on it.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">These
                  type of items can be rolled on by all in attendance.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">Winning
                  a class specific item will not count as winning an open
                  roll.&nbsp; So, if you have won a drop for your class and
                  still have not won an open roll, you will be able to roll on
                  the open item.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">The
                  reverse is also true.&nbsp; Winning an ALL/ALL resist item
                  would not mean that you are ineligible to roll on class
                  specific items as described above.<br>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;</font></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF00"><b>Unusable/Unwanted
              Items<br>
              &nbsp;</b></font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">If
                  an item is unusable or unwanted by any in attendance it will
                  be counted as a sellable.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">From
                  time to time it will be unfortunate that NO DROP items will be
                  destroyed or go to ROT.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">Certain
                  NO DROP quest items such as the items needed for Thurg quest
                  armor will be looted by a guild officer if nobody present can
                  loot it to be randomed at a later time among guild members
                  that can use it.&nbsp; The winner will then win the privilege
                  of multi questing the item with the looter.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF00"><b>Epic
              Drops<br>
              &nbsp;</b></font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">Epic
                  drops will be awarded to the guild member present that is
                  farthest along in their epic.&nbsp; The exception being raids
                  that are specifically scheduled to get a specific piece for a
                  specific person.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">If
                  more than one guild member is in attendance needs the piece
                  and they are at the same stage of their epic, the item will be
                  randomed among them.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">Non-guild
                  participants will not be eligible to loot epic pieces unless
                  all guild members present of that class have the piece.&nbsp;
                  In this event, the item will be randomed off to those
                  non-guild members that are present and need the piece.</font><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99"><br>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;</font></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF00"><b><a name="Miscellaneous">Miscellaneous</a></b></font></p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF00"><b>Compensation<br>
              &nbsp;</b></font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">The
                  RL/RC should have supplies of reagents needed to pass out
                  during the raid, such as peridots</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">Any
                  leftover reagents will be returned to the Guild bank.</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">If
                  the RL/RC does not have a supply of reagents then,&nbsp; all
                  clerics (and other qualifying classes) will be compensated for
                  reagents used during a raid of more than two groups.&nbsp;</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">It
                  will the the raid leader's (or assistant) responsibility to
                  see that this occurs.&nbsp;</font></li>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">It
                  will be the cleric's responsibility to account for moneys
                  spent on reagents during the course of a raid.<br>
                  &nbsp;</font></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF00"><b>Minimum
              levels<br>
              &nbsp;</b></font>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">Level
                  requirements will be posted in the sign-up details for each
                  event.&nbsp; Generally:<br>
                  &nbsp;</font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">Dragon
                      Raids</font>
                      <ul>
                        <li>
                          <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">45
                          for tanks</font></li>
                        <li>
                          <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">47
                          for casters</font></li>
                        <li>
                          <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">39
                          for clerics</font></li>
                        <li>
                          <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">Maximum
                          level for Naggy and Vox is 52<br>
                          </font></li>
                      </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">Planes
                      Raids</font>
                      <ul>
                        <li>
                          <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#FFFF99">Level
                          47 minumum</font></li>
                      </ul>
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p align="left">&nbsp;</p>
          <p align="left">&nbsp;
        </td>
      </tr>
